derivation.yuyuan_name: early 17th cent. (originally denoting a chicken): of unknown origin; probably influenced by the use of biddy denoting an Irish maidservant, from Biddy, pet form of the given name Bridget

entry.def: If someone describes an old woman as an old biddy, they are saying in an unkind way that they think she is silly or unpleasant.

example.ex: We're  not just a lot of old biddies going on about jam.
